<span id="freeTextContainer12047719916056817259">This book is one I believe everyone should read. The subject matter is poignant, still relevant and (given the subject matter) extremely clean. Along with many, this book seems to me a prequel to <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2751.Bret_Easton_Ellis' title='Bret Easton Ellis' rel='nofollow noopener'>Bret Easton Ellis</a>‘s take on hip New York. While finishing it, I considered starting it over from the beginning immediately but have decided to reread <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28676.American_Psycho' title='American Psycho by Bret Easton Ellis' rel='nofollow noopener'>American Psycho</a> first. Bright Lights, Big City is a fast read and I think it is worth your time.</span>
  <span id="freeText12047719916056817259" style="display:none">This book is one I believe everyone should read. The subject matter is poignant, still relevant and (given the subject matter) extremely clean. Along with many, this book seems to me a prequel to <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2751.Bret_Easton_Ellis" title="Bret Easton Ellis" rel="nofollow noopener">Bret Easton Ellis</a>‘s take on hip New York. While finishing it, I considered starting it over from the beginning immediately but have decided to reread <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28676.American_Psycho" title="American Psycho by Bret Easton Ellis" rel="nofollow noopener">American Psycho</a> first. Bright Lights, Big City is a fast read and I think it is worth your time.</span>
