  <span id="freeText16100753419456617084" style="display:none">The ONLY McInerney novel worth reading and a masterpiece of 80's literature, New York is the setting and it's awash with money, excess, fashion, music, clubbing and of course the most important ingredient of all...Bolivian Marching Powder!, or for those not familiar-Cocaine. A brilliant comic morality tale told in first person narrative that is sharp, witty and a whole lot of fun, easily read in a couple of sittings, think American Psycho without the psychotic violence and dark humour and your on the right path. Almost makes you wish for an 80's revival, bring on the big hair, shoulder pads and cheesy pop videos!. </span>
